00:50.025 --> 00:51.526
PRIEST: We are gathered here today

00:51.560 --> 00:54.729
on Jack and Rebecca's
40th wedding anniversary

00:54.763 --> 00:57.337
to witness a renewal of their vows.

00:59.601 --> 01:04.063
synced and corrected by susinz
*www.addic7ed.com*

01:10.400 --> 01:13.087
I hope you're enjoying
your last day as my fiancée,

01:13.112 --> 01:14.937
because by this time tomorrow,

01:14.971 --> 01:16.876
you're gonna be my straight-up wife.

01:19.101 --> 01:20.602
Uh, you doing okay?

01:20.889 --> 01:22.704
Of course. Yeah... why?

01:22.729 --> 01:24.087
Oh, no reason.

01:24.180 --> 01:25.790
You know, just doing
this whole big wedding thing

01:25.815 --> 01:27.493
without your dad's gonna
be hard, and we're here

01:27.518 --> 01:29.626
at the family cabin,
which is probably bringing up

01:29.651 --> 01:31.852
a lot of memories... please
don't <i>Runaway Bride</i> me.

01:32.689 --> 01:34.954
- (QUIETLY): Please don't <i>Runaway Bride...</i>
- Toby. I would never.

01:36.483 --> 01:37.571
But will you come with me?

01:37.596 --> 01:39.275
- I have a surprise for you.
- Ooh.

01:39.300 --> 01:41.001
- KATE: Uh-huh.
- I like surprises.

01:44.629 --> 01:45.868
This is for you.

01:48.423 --> 01:49.602
Oh, look.

01:49.941 --> 01:51.540
It's a used bow tie.

01:51.567 --> 01:53.902
Oh, not just any used bow tie.

01:54.259 --> 01:55.860
This was worn by Leslie Nielsen

01:55.894 --> 01:57.759
in <i>Naked Gun 33 1/3: Final Insult.</i>

01:57.831 --> 02:00.969
- So.
- Shut your freaking face.

02:01.305 --> 02:02.733
- (LAUGHS)
- Leslie Nielsen wore this?

02:02.768 --> 02:03.790
Yeah.

02:03.815 --> 02:05.344
I just wanted to thank you.

02:05.369 --> 02:09.798
You've gone out of your way
to make this my dream wedding.

02:10.524 --> 02:13.837
You know, just one beautiful day
at my favorite place.

02:13.862 --> 02:16.256
And I know that my choices
are kind of...

02:16.281 --> 02:17.321
(SIGHS) they're weird.

02:17.469 --> 02:19.516
I know it's not normal
to have my dad's urn

02:19.541 --> 02:20.868
next to our guestbook.

02:21.126 --> 02:23.266
It's a fun twist on the sign-in station.

02:23.291 --> 02:25.446
Okay, and to have
his Daytona Beach T-shirt

02:25.471 --> 02:26.477
as my something old.

02:26.502 --> 02:28.516
- It's weird, and I know.
- Listen, if my boo comes

02:28.541 --> 02:30.852
with baggage, I'm paying
the handling fee.

02:30.940 --> 02:33.477
- Mm, I love your airline metaphors.
- Well, that's good,

02:33.502 --> 02:35.259
- 'cause I'm cleared for takeoff.
- Oh...

02:35.313 --> 02:36.704
- KEVIN: Yes. Everyone. Okay?
- Aw, damn it.

02:36.729 --> 02:38.821
Everyone gets a Ka-Toby wine opener,

02:38.846 --> 02:40.618
they get a bottle
of champagne and they get

02:40.643 --> 02:42.678
a scented candle, now,
why are you just now starting

02:42.703 --> 02:44.665
with the gift bags?
No, no, no. Hold on, hold on.

02:44.690 --> 02:46.555
Don't justify it, fix it.

02:47.896 --> 02:50.290
Okay. Yeah, I'll see you
tonight, Randall. Okay.

02:52.025 --> 02:53.282
- Wow.
- No, it's fine.

02:53.301 --> 02:55.135
It's fine. Don't worry about it.
Randall and I, we have

02:55.169 --> 02:57.476
this whole, uh, wedding planner
thing all figured out.

02:57.501 --> 02:59.305
You do not have to lift a finger.

03:00.134 --> 03:02.269
Toby, you should be getting
to the airport, all right?

03:02.303 --> 03:03.462
- Your mom gets in at 5:28,
- Oh, yeah.

03:03.487 --> 03:05.821
- your dad gets in at 5:46.
- Yeah, okay, okay, okay.

03:05.846 --> 03:07.899
T-this car ride is gonna be
a nightmare, by the way.

03:07.924 --> 03:10.305
My-my parents, whenever they're
together, all they do is fight.

03:10.330 --> 03:13.540
My dad's constantly pressuring
my mom to marry her boyfriend.

03:14.540 --> 03:15.766
If she marries Monty,

03:15.791 --> 03:17.518
then my dad doesn't
have to pay alimony anymore.

03:17.543 --> 03:19.040
- It's a whole thing.
- Ah.

03:20.876 --> 03:22.188
Okay, I think he wants you to go, babe.

03:22.213 --> 03:23.376
- I think he wants me to leave.
- Yeah.

03:23.401 --> 03:25.517
All right, well,
I'll see you later. Mwah.

03:25.551 --> 03:28.079
I'll see you tomorrow,
at the end of the aisle.

03:28.104 --> 03:29.266
- Thanks for this.
- (KEVIN LAUGHS)

03:29.945 --> 03:31.079
KEVIN: Be safe.

03:37.306 --> 03:39.040
KEVIN: <i>Uh, I'm gonna go
check on these caterers.</i>

03:39.065 --> 03:40.618
Some of these clowns
wouldn't know an amuse-bouche

03:40.643 --> 03:41.759
if it bit them on the ass.

03:41.909 --> 03:43.149
Hey, Kev?

03:43.850 --> 03:45.150
- Yeah.
- Do you think

03:45.175 --> 03:46.743
that, like, Dad would've been okay...

03:47.484 --> 03:49.243
you know, us having it here?

03:50.471 --> 03:51.634
At the cabin?

03:52.084 --> 03:53.126
Yeah.

03:53.710 --> 03:54.930
Dad would've loved it.

04:02.765 --> 04:04.087
(SHUFFLING, CLINKING)

04:06.423 --> 04:07.774
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

04:07.799 --> 04:10.235
Hey, babe. You about ready
to head up to the cabin?

04:10.260 --> 04:11.376
Almost done.

04:11.580 --> 04:13.907
Going as fast as I can.

04:14.833 --> 04:16.540
Got two bottles in one bag.

04:16.565 --> 04:18.188
Get your head out of your ass, Pearson.

04:18.613 --> 04:19.748
You okay?

04:20.009 --> 04:22.407
Just scrambling
to get this done for Kate.

04:22.763 --> 04:24.368
Things have been
a little hectic around here.

04:24.393 --> 04:25.688
Haven't had much time.

04:26.126 --> 04:27.399
Hey, Dej.

04:27.424 --> 04:29.149
You excited about this weekend?

04:30.004 --> 04:31.954
I can't wait for you
to meet my cousin Zoe.

04:31.969 --> 04:34.430
She's gonna take Kate and
Toby's wedding photos.

04:34.579 --> 04:35.641
Yeah, she's the cool one.

04:35.666 --> 04:37.340
In my family, she's the cool one.

04:37.375 --> 04:39.829
Can you believe that I'm not
the cool one in my fa... Okay.

04:39.863 --> 04:41.287
Hey, are you all packed?
We're gonna be leaving

04:41.312 --> 04:42.485
as soon as I finish with these bags.

04:42.510 --> 04:43.626
DEJA: I can't believe we're going

04:43.651 --> 04:45.462
to some dumbass wedding in the woods.

04:48.252 --> 04:49.540
Man, she's mean.

04:50.009 --> 04:51.485
I miss Deja Classic.

04:52.227 --> 04:53.274
No.

04:53.299 --> 04:54.800
Deja Classic was when we first met her,

04:54.825 --> 04:56.430
and she was all quiet and sullen.

04:56.455 --> 05:00.094
I miss Deja 2.0, when she was
all used to us and sweet,

05:00.119 --> 05:01.594
and she told me all my jokes were corny,

05:01.619 --> 05:02.821
but secretly, she liked them.

05:02.906 --> 05:06.808
I feel like the moment she heard
her mom say to the judge

05:06.833 --> 05:09.360
that she wanted to terminate
all parental rights,

05:09.385 --> 05:10.759
something switched in her.

05:10.917 --> 05:12.009
Yep.

05:12.034 --> 05:14.415
Okay. Let's grab the girls and head out.

05:17.231 --> 05:18.454
Uh, wait. Wait.

05:19.703 --> 05:21.048
Can we just do our thing?

05:21.423 --> 05:22.957
Where we say all the bad things

05:22.991 --> 05:24.999
that we're thinking;
no judgment, no censorship?

05:25.024 --> 05:26.446
You want to play
worst-case scenario now?

05:26.471 --> 05:28.126
I just got to get it out of my system.

05:28.493 --> 05:29.579
All right, let's do it.

05:29.614 --> 05:30.712
(EXHALES)

05:31.688 --> 05:34.251
Deja never turns this around
and ends up in jail. Go.

05:34.622 --> 05:36.516
She might kill us both in our sleep. Go.

05:36.794 --> 05:39.555
She might kill us both
not in our sleep. Go.

05:39.679 --> 05:42.247
She'll make Tess resent us
and end up on the pole. Go.

05:42.790 --> 05:44.954
Wait, Tess will resent us, and
Deja will end up on the pole?

05:44.979 --> 05:47.079
Or Tess will resent us,
and also be the one who ends up

05:47.104 --> 05:48.634
- on the pole?
- Both on the pole.

05:48.766 --> 05:49.900
Damn.

05:50.876 --> 05:52.204
Out of your system now?

05:52.673 --> 05:53.719
Yeah.

05:54.456 --> 05:55.782
- Okay.
- Yeah, thanks.

05:56.641 --> 05:58.313
Oh. That's really pretty.

05:58.554 --> 06:00.696
Mm. Nah.

06:01.282 --> 06:03.563
(SIGHING): It's just...
feels a little flashy.

06:03.588 --> 06:05.938
I just-I don't want to do
anything to make Kate feel

06:05.963 --> 06:08.165
like I'm gonna make tomorrow about me.

06:08.190 --> 06:10.313
Wha... Now, why would she think that?

06:11.219 --> 06:15.016
Because I put her on edge
by the things I do or say

06:15.041 --> 06:18.501
or don't say or... the way I breathe.

06:18.651 --> 06:19.844
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

06:20.787 --> 06:22.532
But tomorrow's her wedding day,

06:22.934 --> 06:26.102
and I just feel like I am this
walking reminder of Jack.

06:26.661 --> 06:28.305
You know, he's the one that she lost,

06:28.330 --> 06:31.098
and I'm the one that she got stuck with.

06:31.438 --> 06:34.032
Well, I don't think that's true.

06:34.733 --> 06:37.844
And if it helps, just remember:
at least you're not me.

06:37.869 --> 06:38.907
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

06:39.207 --> 06:40.704
What's that supposed to mean?

06:40.729 --> 06:42.079
- What's that supposed to mean?
- Yeah.

06:42.104 --> 06:44.798
Well, if anyone is a walking
reminder of Jack, it's me.

06:45.299 --> 06:46.469
Forget about what you're wearing.

06:46.494 --> 06:48.266
If I could dress in all brown tomorrow

06:48.291 --> 06:49.423
and pretend to be a tree, I would.

06:49.704 --> 06:51.471
- (LAUGHS) Stop.
- Just throw acorns at people.

06:52.200 --> 06:53.258
Miguel.

06:53.629 --> 06:54.782
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

06:59.597 --> 07:01.063
- (ENGINE STOPS)
- (DOOR CLOSES)

07:01.720 --> 07:03.571
- Hey, bud. What's up, man?
- (KEVIN CLAPS)

07:03.923 --> 07:05.149
Welcome to wedding central.

07:05.736 --> 07:07.477
Where is everybody?
Where's Beth, the girls?

07:07.608 --> 07:08.875
I dropped them at the hotel.

07:09.088 --> 07:10.118
It was a rough car ride.

07:10.143 --> 07:11.508
- Really? Deja?
- Yeah.

07:11.954 --> 07:12.985
She's belligerent.

07:13.010 --> 07:14.410
It's like I'm raising Russell Crowe.

07:14.435 --> 07:15.414
- (LAUGHS)
- KATE: Kevin?

07:15.479 --> 07:17.258
- Kevin!
- Uh-oh.

07:18.084 --> 07:19.149
(GRUNTS)

07:21.258 --> 07:22.500
No. No.

07:22.525 --> 07:23.859
No. No, no, no, no, no.

07:24.088 --> 07:25.618
- Hey.
- What's up?

07:25.892 --> 07:28.594
- Um, hey, Randall.
- Okay, sis, what's up?

07:28.619 --> 07:29.786
- Oh, my God, oh, my God.
- You all right?

07:30.134 --> 07:32.352
Um, I can't find Dad's Daytona T-shirt.

07:32.377 --> 07:33.524
It was gonna be my something old,

07:33.549 --> 07:34.571
and I was gonna pin it in my dress.

07:34.596 --> 07:36.330
- Aw.
- Wow, that's really, uh...

07:36.586 --> 07:40.063
- Weird? I know I am weird, Randall!
- KEVIN: Ah, no, no, no.

07:40.088 --> 07:41.477
- "Unique." I was gonna say "unique."
- Hold up. Wait, wa...

07:41.502 --> 07:42.938
- Was what I thought.
- Kate. Kate.

07:43.249 --> 07:45.211
- What if Toby never packed it?
- You know what we're gonna do?

07:45.236 --> 07:46.907
- Just call Toby. We're gonna call Toby.
- Yeah. We...

07:46.932 --> 07:48.313
- It's a quick phone call. Quick fix.
- Yeah, yeah.

07:48.338 --> 07:49.664
- We'll...
- Do not...

07:50.412 --> 07:51.961
- tell him that I'm freaking out.
- Who's freaking out?

07:51.986 --> 07:54.008
- No.
- I do not want him to worry about me.

07:54.033 --> 07:55.336
It's a quick phone call. Yeah.

07:55.361 --> 07:56.422
(WHISTLES)

07:57.290 --> 07:59.562
ALAN: I'm just saying, you two
have been dating for a while

07:59.587 --> 08:02.218
now, so why don't you just marry
the poor bastard already?

08:02.243 --> 08:04.241
As I told you before, Alan,

08:04.266 --> 08:06.828
- Monty and I are taking it slow.
- Yeah, you mean

08:06.853 --> 08:09.213
like the way you're slowly
draining my retirement fund

08:09.238 --> 08:11.399
- with those alimony payments.
- TOBY: Okay, guys, it's, uh,

08:11.424 --> 08:13.719
it's my wedding weekend,
so can we go 48 hours

08:13.744 --> 08:15.094
- without talking about alimony?
- (PHONE RINGING)

08:15.344 --> 08:16.750
Hey, look, it's Kevin.

08:16.775 --> 08:18.602
- Hey, Kev.
- KEVIN (OVER PHONE): <i>Toby.</i>

08:18.627 --> 08:20.071
<i>- 'Sup?
- 'Sup?</i>

08:20.950 --> 08:22.946
I got Randall here.
Randall wants to say 'sup.

08:24.418 --> 08:26.063
- 'Sup.
- 'Sup.

08:26.180 --> 08:27.680
KEVIN: <i>We were just calling,
we wanted to know</i>

08:27.705 --> 08:28.852
if you could remember where you packed

08:28.877 --> 08:30.391
our dad's Daytona T-shirt.

08:32.696 --> 08:34.703
Oh, my God, did I forget
to pack the T-shirt?

08:34.727 --> 08:37.383
I totally forgot to pack the T-shirt.

08:37.741 --> 08:38.938
<i>Uh, uh, okay,</i>

08:38.962 --> 08:41.102
um, I can figure out
a way to get it. Uh, uh...

08:41.126 --> 08:42.836
- There's still time.
- It's fine. Everything's fine.

08:42.861 --> 08:44.680
<i>- Everything is great, um...
- Really?</i>

08:44.945 --> 08:46.453
<i>Yeah, really.</i> Um...

08:47.383 --> 08:48.571
...it's no biggie.

08:49.995 --> 08:52.813
- Ciao.
- Uh, uh... okay, bye.

08:52.927 --> 08:54.055
(PHONE BEEPS)

08:55.075 --> 08:56.157
(SIGHS)

08:57.352 --> 08:59.618
Hey, it sounds like
it's just a shirt, right?

08:59.643 --> 09:01.821
Yeah, well, it's not just a shirt, Ma.

09:06.091 --> 09:08.711
RANDALL: Okay. We'll round up
anything of Dad's we can find,

09:08.736 --> 09:10.813
and then, tomorrow morning,
you'll take your pick.

09:10.909 --> 09:12.000
Okay?

09:13.048 --> 09:14.071
Kate.

09:14.096 --> 09:15.157
It's a T-shirt.

09:15.427 --> 09:16.821
We can roll with this, right?

09:17.544 --> 09:19.422
He was more than a T-shirt.

09:20.311 --> 09:21.344
Okay?

09:22.590 --> 09:23.890
- Okay.
- Okay.

09:24.721 --> 09:26.078
Okay, so then, uh,

09:26.103 --> 09:27.993
you just put your PJs on, all right?

09:28.432 --> 09:30.289
Curl up with your favorite
Sandra Bullock movie,

09:30.314 --> 09:32.282
- because guess what.
- Hmm?

09:32.307 --> 09:33.942
- Someone's getting married tomorrow.
- RANDALL: Yeah.

09:33.967 --> 09:34.977
- Who?
- Right?

09:35.002 --> 09:36.243
- Who's getting married tomorrow?
- (LAUGHS)

09:36.268 --> 09:37.547
- Ah.
- All right.

09:37.572 --> 09:38.618
KEVIN: Mm.

09:39.119 --> 09:40.452
- All right.
- RANDALL: Okay.

09:40.477 --> 09:42.328
One of the romantic ones.
Not the one where

09:42.353 --> 09:44.602
they're trying to kill her
through the Internet. Spooky.

09:52.493 --> 09:54.039
JACK: So some of you may not know this

09:54.056 --> 09:56.827
but for the 22 years that
I worked for Lundy Builders,

09:56.852 --> 10:01.381
my wife put a folded note packed
into my briefcase every day.

10:01.406 --> 10:02.606
(REBECCA CHUCKLES)

10:02.782 --> 10:05.132
The highlight of my day in the office

10:05.649 --> 10:07.975
was opening one of those
little scraps of paper.

10:08.672 --> 10:11.743
Now, when Rebecca and I started
Big Three Homes,

10:12.391 --> 10:14.735
she stopped writing the lunch notes.

10:15.688 --> 10:17.803
But I was okay with that.

10:17.828 --> 10:23.297
I had the highlight of my day
right there, sitting by my side.

10:24.081 --> 10:25.266
Every day.

10:28.203 --> 10:29.352
Uh-huh.

10:29.891 --> 10:32.193
All right, we got nine hours
until I-do's, people.

10:32.227 --> 10:34.662
Little less texting, a lot more tenting.

10:36.962 --> 10:38.095
BETH: I was.

10:38.352 --> 10:39.703
All right, ladies, let's go.

10:39.728 --> 10:41.663
- Come on, ladies.
- (RANDALL GROANS)

10:45.782 --> 10:47.108
This place is a dump.

10:48.469 --> 10:49.696
Aunt Zoe!

10:50.002 --> 10:52.039
ZOE: Hey, T-bone. Hey, A-frame.

10:52.719 --> 10:54.016
- You look so good.
- Look at you!

10:54.041 --> 10:55.650
Oh, you look great. How are you?

10:55.675 --> 10:57.436
- Thank you.
- Hey, Zoe.

10:57.461 --> 10:58.703
- Hey!
- How you doing?

10:58.728 --> 11:00.508
- I'm good.
- Good. Girls,

11:00.533 --> 11:02.672
will you take your dresses
inside for me, please.

11:02.697 --> 11:03.455
Yes.

11:03.480 --> 11:05.571
Thank you very much. Appreciate it.

11:05.814 --> 11:08.539
Uh, I'm gonna go see
if Kevin needs anything.

11:08.564 --> 11:10.172
I love you. Mwah.

11:12.566 --> 11:15.391
So, you're just gonna,
like, look 21 forever?

11:15.441 --> 11:17.196
- That's your thing?
- Look who's talking.

11:17.609 --> 11:20.430
You got no right to still have
that body after two kids.

11:21.646 --> 11:22.953
(BOTH LAUGHING)

11:25.624 --> 11:27.625
- Oh, you good?
- Oh, I'm good.

11:27.650 --> 11:30.016
Yeah? I don't have to come to
Chicago and whup nobody's ass?

11:30.041 --> 11:31.942
- Mm, not this week.
- Okay.

11:32.953 --> 11:34.698
Thank you for doing this wedding, lady.

11:34.805 --> 11:37.118
Hey, any family of yours is mine, right?

11:38.089 --> 11:39.782
This is why I love you.

11:41.774 --> 11:43.000
Is that her?

11:43.227 --> 11:45.219
Mm-hmm. I'll tell you all about it.

11:45.586 --> 11:47.289
- Hopefully, over champagne.
- Mm.

11:47.314 --> 11:49.508
- Lots of champagne.
- Mm-mm. (CHUCKLES)

11:51.821 --> 11:53.749
All right, here it is,
everything old of Dad's

11:53.774 --> 11:56.157
I could find around the cabin
to replace the T-shirt.

11:56.922 --> 11:58.422
RANDALL: So you want her
to walk down the aisle

11:58.447 --> 11:59.930
with our old baseball bat.

12:01.461 --> 12:02.532
That's romantic.

12:02.985 --> 12:04.711
Yeah, you're right...
this is a disaster.

12:04.736 --> 12:06.391
A total disaster, man.
How are we gonna do...

12:06.416 --> 12:09.102
- KEVIN: Hey! Look, it's the bride!
- Hey.

12:09.172 --> 12:11.139
Uh, so we rounded up a few

12:11.164 --> 12:12.758
- "something old" options for you
- Yeah.

12:12.783 --> 12:13.961
to replace the T-shirt.
What do you think?

12:13.986 --> 12:15.047
- Terrific options.
- Mm-hmm.

12:15.072 --> 12:17.250
Thank you. But I don't need
any of this stuff.

12:17.275 --> 12:18.868
- I have a new plan.
- What do you mean, new plan?

12:18.893 --> 12:20.044
What... Where are you going?

12:20.219 --> 12:22.219
You know, Mom's gonna be here
with the bridesmaids, they're gonna do

12:22.244 --> 12:23.352
hair and makeup any minute now.

12:23.377 --> 12:26.141
- Okay. I'll be back soon.
- REBECCA: Hello, hello.

12:26.472 --> 12:27.711
- KEVIN: Hey.
- Bug!

12:28.299 --> 12:30.641
Happy wedding day, sweetheart.

12:30.666 --> 12:31.922
I'm just running an errand.

12:32.272 --> 12:34.438
Oh. Can somebody not run
the errand for you?

12:34.463 --> 12:35.602
I'll be back.

12:36.068 --> 12:37.110
(DOOR OPENS)

12:37.421 --> 12:38.758
- Did I say something wrong?
- (DOOR CLOSES)

12:38.868 --> 12:40.453
You said, "Happy wedding day, Bug."

12:40.478 --> 12:42.680
It's wedding day, bitches!

12:43.608 --> 12:45.409
Oh, I thought this room would be, like,

12:45.434 --> 12:46.727
- filled with women.
- RANDALL: No.

12:48.237 --> 12:49.352
Where is Kate?

12:50.028 --> 12:51.219
♪

13:06.369 --> 13:08.305
MAN: Hey! Welcome to Artisanal Scoops.

13:08.357 --> 13:09.774
Would you like a sample
of our new flavor?

13:09.799 --> 13:11.008
It's lavender balsamic.

13:11.600 --> 13:12.907
Um, no. Thanks.

13:13.493 --> 13:15.266
Uh, I used to come here with my dad.

13:15.345 --> 13:17.047
I think it was called Frenchie's
back then, or...

13:17.072 --> 13:19.657
Oh, yeah. They sold the place
a couple years ago.

13:21.547 --> 13:23.039
Oh. Any chance you guys are still making

13:23.064 --> 13:24.344
that banana pudding flavor?

13:24.453 --> 13:25.688
No. I'm sorry.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.243
It was my dad's favorite.

13:29.268 --> 13:30.303
I was gonna buy it today

13:30.328 --> 13:32.149
to serve with the cake at my wedding.

13:33.028 --> 13:34.914
Not exactly something <i>old,</i> but

13:35.287 --> 13:36.594
an old tradition.

13:38.229 --> 13:39.899
Hey, we do have banana coconut.

13:39.969 --> 13:41.672
It's really good.
It's one of my favorites.

13:42.369 --> 13:43.766
No. Thanks.

13:45.600 --> 13:46.696
<i>It just wouldn't...</i>

13:46.990 --> 13:48.196
<i>mean anything.</i>

13:49.511 --> 13:50.797
But thanks.

13:51.412 --> 13:52.680
♪

14:07.040 --> 14:10.258
So, long before Jack and I
had our own company,

14:10.634 --> 14:12.836
and long before the Big Three
were around,

14:13.352 --> 14:15.038
I was singing

14:15.126 --> 14:16.289
in a bar...

14:16.921 --> 14:18.391
when a man walked in.

14:21.015 --> 14:22.297
(GENTLE INTRO PLAYS)

14:23.948 --> 14:25.086
♪

14:29.587 --> 14:33.555
♪ <i>I'm bein' followed by a moonshadow</i> ♪

14:33.836 --> 14:37.060
♪ <i>Moonshadow, moonshadow</i> ♪

14:38.000 --> 14:42.118
♪ <i>Leapin' and hoppin' on a moonshadow</i> ♪

14:42.399 --> 14:45.664
♪ <i>Moonshadow, moonshadow</i> ♪

14:46.470 --> 14:50.407
♪ <i>And if I ever lose my hands</i> ♪

14:50.999 --> 14:54.602
♪ <i>Lose my plough, lose my land</i> ♪

14:54.729 --> 14:57.485
(AUDIO FADING): ♪ <i>Oh, if I
ever lose my hands, oh...</i> ♪

15:00.672 --> 15:02.085
Hey-o!

15:02.750 --> 15:03.914
REBECCA: Hey.

15:04.024 --> 15:06.436
- What is going on in here, Randall?
- Mm-hmm.

15:06.461 --> 15:08.678
I did not know that Kate hired
professional models

15:08.703 --> 15:10.030
- to be her bridesmaids.
- (LAUGHTER)

15:10.055 --> 15:11.928
I think she did, Kev, 'cause this room's

15:11.962 --> 15:14.141
- full of a whole lot of damn.
- BETH: Yeah, it is.

15:14.344 --> 15:15.828
- What do we got?
- (LAUGHS) Thank you.

15:15.853 --> 15:17.844
- For you.
- We brought gifts. For you.

15:19.399 --> 15:22.055
- RANDALL: Don't even try.
- KEVIN: Mom? Yeah.

15:22.080 --> 15:24.607
So, uh, I just tried her again,
and her phone must be off,

15:24.642 --> 15:26.102
'cause it went straight to voice mail.

15:26.743 --> 15:28.594
- (SIGHS) We should go look for her.
- Where?

15:28.914 --> 15:31.289
- I have an idea.
- Uh... Whoop! (CHUCKLES)

15:31.749 --> 15:34.617
Uh, I'm maid of honor.
I should help search.

15:34.735 --> 15:36.619
Maid of honor. Oh. I thought Kate said

15:36.654 --> 15:38.172
she didn't have a maid of honor.

15:38.500 --> 15:40.957
Well, maybe she said that,
but she didn't mean it.

15:41.500 --> 15:42.758
(CHUCKLING)

15:44.289 --> 15:46.321
- We could... could, you know...
- No.

15:46.346 --> 15:47.774
- Really?
- Yeah. We're good.

15:48.219 --> 15:49.500
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

15:49.665 --> 15:50.852
Okay (MUTTERS, CHUCKLES)

15:52.875 --> 15:54.477
- Oh, man. She's crazy.
- Yeah, man.

15:54.502 --> 15:55.758
Don't let me sleep with her.

15:56.509 --> 15:59.618
So now we're waiting
for the courts to terminate

15:59.643 --> 16:02.278
her mom's parental rights so
that we can legally adopt her.

16:02.625 --> 16:06.016
But she has turned
into a complete nightmare.

16:06.158 --> 16:08.026
I can barely get a sentence out of her.

16:08.360 --> 16:09.602
And I'm pretty sure she's wearing

16:09.627 --> 16:12.000
- that sweatshirt to Kate's wedding.
- Yikes.

16:12.330 --> 16:14.907
- Mm.
- You want me to try talking to her?

16:15.953 --> 16:17.938
What are you, like,
the angry kid whisperer now?

16:18.718 --> 16:20.727
Only 'cause I used to be the angry kid.

16:25.331 --> 16:26.579
(DOOR CREAKS)

16:26.604 --> 16:27.961
Can't believe we missed her.

16:29.956 --> 16:32.399
God, this Nutella chip is insane, huh?

16:32.424 --> 16:33.891
Ridonkulously good.

16:34.163 --> 16:35.375
This is just so good.

16:38.215 --> 16:40.282
- Mm. (GRUNTS)
- Do not drip ice cream in my car.

16:40.307 --> 16:42.428
I'm not. I'm not gonna drip ice
cream in the car, okay? It's...

16:42.453 --> 16:44.554
I understand. You love the car.
You bought it for cash.

16:44.735 --> 16:45.875
- Thank you.
- Where are we going?

16:45.985 --> 16:46.985
No idea.

16:48.664 --> 16:50.193
This is a disaster, Randall.

16:50.227 --> 16:52.469
This is huge. We lost the bride
on the wedding day? All right?

16:52.494 --> 16:54.407
That's, like, the number one
don't for wedding coordinators.

16:54.432 --> 16:55.516
Yeah.

16:58.016 --> 17:00.203
You know, Beth and I play
this game sometimes,

17:00.743 --> 17:02.243
worst-case scenario.

17:02.399 --> 17:05.208
It's where we say all the things
that we're afraid of out loud,

17:05.242 --> 17:07.391
and it makes us feel better. You know?

17:07.555 --> 17:09.414
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm down.
- Okay.

17:11.711 --> 17:13.116
(SIGHS) We never find Kate

17:13.727 --> 17:16.118
and we have to tell Toby
that the wedding's off

17:16.438 --> 17:20.102
and he's so shocked that he has
a heart attack and dies.

17:21.477 --> 17:24.027
- Jesus, Randall.
- That's-that's the game.

17:24.060 --> 17:25.250
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

17:26.344 --> 17:28.188
You know, what if he
doesn't die, Randall?

17:28.213 --> 17:29.172
Okay.

17:29.237 --> 17:31.758
- But, uh...
- (CLEARS THROAT)

17:32.391 --> 17:33.883
I mean, he could kick
her out of the apartment.

17:33.908 --> 17:34.610
(WHISTLES)

17:34.635 --> 17:35.483
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

17:35.508 --> 17:37.382
Now she's forced to
find a place to live.

17:37.407 --> 17:38.908
She's forced to move
in with me, all right?

17:38.943 --> 17:40.276
It's supposed to be
temporary, of course,

17:40.311 --> 17:42.680
- but neither one of us ever find love.
- Mm.

17:42.860 --> 17:45.815
Right? We become one
of those creepy pairs of twins

17:45.849 --> 17:47.180
that grows old together.

17:47.602 --> 17:49.018
And we're at the grocery store

17:49.053 --> 17:50.727
and people mistake us
for a married couple

17:50.752 --> 17:52.722
and we don't even correct 'em
anymore because...

17:52.756 --> 17:54.993
(CHUCKLES) I mean, what's the point?

17:55.259 --> 17:56.274
Wow.

17:56.438 --> 17:58.274
- You're really good at this game.
- Thank you.

17:58.299 --> 17:59.493
You're welcome.

18:03.930 --> 18:05.664
Hey, what if, after Dad died,

18:06.969 --> 18:09.508
I got so absorbed in my own life,

18:10.674 --> 18:13.430
with school and Beth
and the girls, that, um,

18:14.435 --> 18:16.399
I stopped looking out for my sister?

18:23.094 --> 18:24.164
What if...

18:25.253 --> 18:26.352
uh...

18:28.586 --> 18:30.696
what if she spent so much time
taking care of me

18:30.721 --> 18:32.375
that she forgot to take care of herself?

18:34.375 --> 18:36.414
And year after year went by
and I should've...

18:38.352 --> 18:40.461
(SIGHS) recognized
and I should've helped her?

18:42.754 --> 18:43.961
I didn't help her.

18:49.649 --> 18:50.821
(INHALES SHARPLY)

18:52.297 --> 18:53.750
(SIGHS) Randall, I do not feel better.

18:54.163 --> 18:55.445
No.

19:03.227 --> 19:04.414
♪

19:32.751 --> 19:34.125
Not big on weddings?

19:35.368 --> 19:36.618
Me neither, actually.

19:36.822 --> 19:38.625
I just do them to pay the bills, but...

19:39.297 --> 19:40.602
(SIGHS) not really my jam.

19:41.408 --> 19:43.211
They're just so in your face, you know?

19:45.061 --> 19:46.429
At least there's cake.

19:48.899 --> 19:51.110
I hope at least Randall
does a good toast.

19:51.672 --> 19:53.024
I'm a sucker for a good toast.

19:53.049 --> 19:54.618
Listen, you don't got to talk to me.

19:55.544 --> 19:58.610
Okay? You're Annie
and Tess' aunt, not mine.

19:58.871 --> 20:00.274
I'm not theirs either, actually.

20:01.321 --> 20:02.875
Beth is my cousin,

20:03.625 --> 20:05.414
so, technically, that makes...

20:06.272 --> 20:08.157
Tess and Annie my...

20:08.369 --> 20:09.985
first cousins once removed.

20:11.056 --> 20:12.594
But the girls like to
call me their aunt,

20:12.619 --> 20:14.633
'cause, Beth, she's like a sister to me.

20:15.315 --> 20:16.789
'Cause her mom raised me.

20:18.643 --> 20:21.883
My mom dumped me in their house

20:21.908 --> 20:23.243
when I was seven or eight.

20:23.782 --> 20:25.149
Said she'd be back in a few weeks.

20:25.174 --> 20:26.493
I know what you're trying to do.

20:27.982 --> 20:29.727
I don't care if my mom left me.

20:30.071 --> 20:32.211
Well, good for you. But I did.

20:33.122 --> 20:35.594
I was so angry, I wanted to take
it out on the whole world.

20:36.978 --> 20:38.953
Instead, I took it out on Beth's mom

20:39.614 --> 20:41.969
and on Beth, on her whole family.

20:43.688 --> 20:44.883
You know, somehow,

20:44.973 --> 20:47.118
it was my way of being loyal to <i>my</i> mom.

20:49.035 --> 20:51.164
God, I got real good

20:51.363 --> 20:53.414
making their lives miserable.

20:59.432 --> 21:02.352
Then, one morning, I don't know...

21:05.371 --> 21:06.539
I just forgot.

21:08.762 --> 21:10.141
I forgot to hate 'em.

21:13.690 --> 21:14.977
We were all, um...

21:15.961 --> 21:17.188
sitting at the kitchen table,

21:17.213 --> 21:19.844
and Beth was saying something crazy,

21:20.035 --> 21:21.402
probably about D'Angelo.

21:23.869 --> 21:25.289
And I started laughing.

21:27.342 --> 21:28.657
That was a good day.

21:32.047 --> 21:35.532
The day... when it stopped
making sense...

21:37.370 --> 21:39.282
...hating the people who loved me.

21:40.904 --> 21:42.125
♪

21:44.348 --> 21:45.610
(SIGHS)

21:46.532 --> 21:48.860
Now, if you'll excuse me, I gotta go...

21:49.473 --> 21:52.680
find some pretty light and
photograph the bride's shoes.

21:54.154 --> 21:56.391
Did I mention weddings are not my thing?

22:03.665 --> 22:07.422
My love for you abounds,
and a heart attack

22:07.481 --> 22:09.763
- and two proposals later... Yeah? Yup.
- (KNOCK ON DOOR)

22:13.742 --> 22:16.575
Hey there. Come on in, parentals.

22:17.684 --> 22:20.036
- Hey, how you doing?
- Doing good.

22:20.061 --> 22:22.504
Was up half the night
calling Task Rabbits,

22:22.529 --> 22:24.614
trying to convince them
to fly Kate's dad's

22:24.639 --> 22:26.817
- T-shirt across the country.
- Yeah, we know.

22:26.977 --> 22:28.215
That's why you couldn't
have dinner with us.

22:28.240 --> 22:29.840
Yeah, in the end, they all said no.

22:29.865 --> 22:33.786
So, apparently they are
"not up to the Task" Rabbits.

22:33.811 --> 22:34.856
(LAUGHS)

22:34.997 --> 22:36.664
- Can you help me with this?
- Yeah.

22:38.588 --> 22:42.465
Um... your mother and I,
we need you to know

22:42.490 --> 22:45.317
that we have concerns about Kate.

22:46.351 --> 22:48.246
Wha... What? Why? Stop.

22:50.205 --> 22:51.442
You barely know her.

22:52.646 --> 22:55.934
Well, it feels like you're constantly

22:55.959 --> 22:58.715
bending over backwards to calm her.

22:59.298 --> 23:02.028
Okay, yeah, it-it's...
you guys, it's a wedding.

23:02.062 --> 23:03.543
It's supposed to be a little stressful.

23:03.568 --> 23:05.582
Yeah, but the way you tiptoe around

23:05.855 --> 23:08.661
to keep from setting her off,
it's just not normal, honey.

23:08.881 --> 23:11.434
And it feels to us like she...

23:11.459 --> 23:13.645
she might be a little unstable.

23:13.670 --> 23:16.012
Wow. Un-Unstable?

23:16.180 --> 23:19.106
Do-Do you remember when she broke
up with you for no reason,

23:19.131 --> 23:21.536
and you had to fly across the
country to change her mind?

23:21.561 --> 23:22.918
Okay, that wasn't for no reason.

23:22.943 --> 23:24.051
Look, Toby...

23:25.166 --> 23:27.270
I didn't say anything when you
married your first wife.

23:27.295 --> 23:28.465
- Dad...
- No!

23:28.571 --> 23:29.805
You need to hear this.

23:29.901 --> 23:31.918
Now, I knew Josie wasn't good for you,

23:31.943 --> 23:33.348
and I held my tongue.

23:35.096 --> 23:37.481
And now you're gonna marry
this new woman who...

23:37.967 --> 23:40.262
clearly has issues you can't fix.

23:40.287 --> 23:42.645
And we're worried that you're
headed down the same path.

23:42.670 --> 23:44.770
Toby, you remember... you-you remember

23:45.200 --> 23:48.450
what it was like when
things fell apart with Josie.

23:49.676 --> 23:52.981
Remember how you stopped going to work,

23:53.006 --> 23:56.153
and how I-I-I found you

23:56.178 --> 23:58.684
in your apartment
in the middle of a workday

23:59.143 --> 24:01.848
just with the curtains drawn
and just-just...

24:02.845 --> 24:05.536
hiding under the covers
like a little kid.

24:06.716 --> 24:07.926
(MARY SIGHS)

24:08.781 --> 24:10.864
Oh, sweetie, you were severely depressed

24:10.889 --> 24:14.254
for a very long time, and we-we just...

24:14.279 --> 24:15.543
You know what's funny?

24:16.765 --> 24:17.895
Is that my whole life,

24:17.920 --> 24:20.387
I wanted you two to agree on something,

24:21.612 --> 24:23.926
and now you finally do.

24:25.146 --> 24:27.590
Here we are. Y-you-you agree that

24:27.615 --> 24:30.153
I shouldn't marry the woman
that I'm madly in love with.

24:30.178 --> 24:32.309
- Toby, son...
- No, Dad, listen.

24:32.334 --> 24:34.286
I think you need to hear this.

24:34.358 --> 24:37.371
Kate is not like Josie. All right?

24:37.396 --> 24:38.590
She would never hurt me.

24:38.615 --> 24:39.934
She cares about me.

24:40.735 --> 24:43.496
So, yeah, the wedding may be
bringing some stuff up,

24:43.521 --> 24:46.754
but it's not because she's unstable.

24:46.779 --> 24:49.918
Okay, if anyone's unstable,
I'm the unstable one, right?

24:50.970 --> 24:54.200
Fine, I'm unstably in love
with-with Kate Pearson.

24:56.331 --> 24:58.418
So, here is what's gonna happen.

24:58.443 --> 25:00.614
You two are gonna go downstairs,
you're gonna make a decision.

25:01.807 --> 25:04.528
All right, you're gonna decide
that-that coming to me like this

25:04.553 --> 25:06.353
was-was a terrible mistake.

25:06.913 --> 25:09.246
All right, and you're gonna show
up to my wedding with bells on.

25:09.271 --> 25:10.387
Or you can decide to

25:10.412 --> 25:11.543
go straight on to the airport.

25:12.075 --> 25:13.409
Either way, in about an hour,

25:13.434 --> 25:14.868
I'm gonna be standing
out on the front lawn

25:14.893 --> 25:16.794
watching my bride walk down the aisle.

25:16.819 --> 25:19.926
So... okay? Okay.

25:19.951 --> 25:22.192
Uh, please go.

25:24.450 --> 25:27.114
I mean, please help me
with this last cuff link,

25:27.139 --> 25:28.262
and then go.

25:30.992 --> 25:32.020
(SIGHS)

25:34.645 --> 25:35.754
(DOOR OPENS)

25:39.027 --> 25:40.379
Don't you look b...

25:41.052 --> 25:43.582
- Uh, still no word from Kate?
- No.

25:44.256 --> 25:45.395
(PHONE RINGING)

25:45.420 --> 25:46.614
- Wait.
- Oh.

25:49.120 --> 25:50.364
Hi, Bug.

25:51.238 --> 25:53.839
- KATE: Hey, Mom.
- REBECCA: <i>Where are you?</i>

25:58.486 --> 26:00.200
Okay, I've been having these dreams

26:00.363 --> 26:02.582
every night for the past
couple of weeks.

26:03.154 --> 26:05.512
We're at the cabin, at a wedding but...

26:06.265 --> 26:08.473
but it's not me and Toby, Mom. It's...

26:09.126 --> 26:10.411
it's you and Dad,

26:10.436 --> 26:12.106
<i>and you're renewing your vows.</i>

26:15.218 --> 26:17.614
<i>And you're so beautiful and...</i>

26:18.741 --> 26:20.911
<i>and Dad is older and grayer,</i>

26:20.936 --> 26:22.136
but still Dad.

26:22.410 --> 26:23.528
And,

26:24.680 --> 26:26.614
<i>you know, we're just... we're all there.</i>

26:27.100 --> 26:29.645
<i>And we're so happy together.</i>

26:30.323 --> 26:31.426
♪

26:35.404 --> 26:37.496
You know, the way it was supposed to be.

26:39.862 --> 26:41.020
(SIGHS)

26:41.419 --> 26:42.528
Wow.

26:43.292 --> 26:45.278
That sounds really
beautiful, sweetheart.

26:45.816 --> 26:48.239
<i>You know, weddings
can be very emotional.</i>

26:48.264 --> 26:50.473
They stir all kinds of things up.

26:50.941 --> 26:53.801
But that's why I'm glad
you have Toby now,

26:54.595 --> 26:56.653
to go through these kinds
of things with.

26:58.452 --> 27:00.098
<i>What was he doing in the dreams?</i>

27:00.416 --> 27:02.434
Probably making you laugh somehow, huh?

27:04.668 --> 27:06.075
No, he's not in them.

27:06.504 --> 27:07.528
Oh.

27:09.378 --> 27:10.926
Is that bad, that he's not in them?

27:10.951 --> 27:12.293
No, no, no. It's fine.

27:12.318 --> 27:15.418
I just, I figured, because,
you know, the wedding.

27:16.450 --> 27:18.496
<i>- You know, you...
- I got to go, Mom.</i>

27:19.388 --> 27:20.575
(EXHALES)

27:31.900 --> 27:33.071
♪

28:15.439 --> 28:18.907
I don't know why Toby hasn't
been in the dreams I'm having.

28:21.659 --> 28:24.228
But I do know that he is
the perfect guy for me, though.

28:26.596 --> 28:27.642
With...

28:28.434 --> 28:30.196
Without a doubt in my mind,

28:30.221 --> 28:33.556
and you wouldn't...
you wouldn't, either.

28:37.763 --> 28:40.398
You remember the carnival that
would come to town every summer

28:40.423 --> 28:42.579
with those old roller coasters?

28:45.149 --> 28:47.116
Oh, I loved riding those with you.

28:48.276 --> 28:51.517
I... Feeling so scared, but
so safe, all at the same time.

28:55.198 --> 28:57.032
I've been holding onto that feeling

28:57.057 --> 28:58.845
for a really long time now.

28:59.639 --> 29:00.899
(SIGHS)

29:01.914 --> 29:03.954
That feeling of you next to me.

29:05.277 --> 29:06.501
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

29:10.000 --> 29:11.043
But, Dad...

29:12.454 --> 29:14.110
I'm getting married today.

29:14.408 --> 29:15.438
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

29:15.463 --> 29:16.587
Ooh.

29:16.940 --> 29:19.493
And I've got to make room.

29:19.617 --> 29:21.321
I've got to make room for Toby.

29:21.553 --> 29:24.922
So I've got to... I've got
to let go a little now.

29:47.096 --> 29:48.931
How long have you guys been here?

29:49.077 --> 29:50.431
RANDALL: Just a few minutes.

29:50.550 --> 29:52.337
Seemed like you were having a moment.

29:53.387 --> 29:55.110
So you did it?

29:58.315 --> 30:00.290
I did. I did.

30:01.791 --> 30:03.345
Let's go get me married.

30:08.830 --> 30:10.758
You know, maybe we didn't
fail her after all.

30:10.783 --> 30:11.966
Are you kidding me?

30:12.000 --> 30:13.205
We're great brothers.

30:13.230 --> 30:14.423
- We are.
- (SCOFFS)

30:14.624 --> 30:16.792
- KATE: You guys. Guys!
- I would want me as a brother.

30:16.842 --> 30:17.906
Need to get married, here.

30:17.931 --> 30:18.778
- KEVIN: Oh.
- RANDALL: Gotcha.

30:18.803 --> 30:20.112
- Let's get married, here.
- Let's do that, let's do that.

30:23.049 --> 30:24.443
KEVIN: Oh, this is gonna be great.

30:29.000 --> 30:30.982
- What are you doing?
- Guarding the door.

30:31.855 --> 30:33.709
Why are you making that cocky smile?

30:44.384 --> 30:45.709
What am I seeing?

30:46.076 --> 30:47.584
Did she just have a pretty dress on,

30:47.609 --> 30:48.717
and some lip gloss?

30:48.742 --> 30:49.764
We had a talk.

30:50.268 --> 30:52.467
Don't expect her to do
The Electric Slide tonight,

30:52.492 --> 30:54.951
but, uh, if we're lucky,
we might get a sentence or two.

30:55.455 --> 30:57.178
Good Lord, I love my baby cousin.

30:57.779 --> 30:59.279
- (CHUCKLES)
- Oh, thank you.

31:02.651 --> 31:03.787
Oh, Kate.

31:04.661 --> 31:05.803
Hi.

31:06.943 --> 31:09.709
You look stunning.

31:09.734 --> 31:11.436
That dress is just...

31:13.318 --> 31:14.381
Perfect.

31:14.475 --> 31:16.709
I mean, it's gonna be perfect
in the setting.

31:16.734 --> 31:18.162
Not that it wouldn't be perfect anywhere

31:18.187 --> 31:19.482
because it's a beautiful dress.

31:19.507 --> 31:20.764
- Mom.
- But it's...

31:21.350 --> 31:24.779
- I know. Are you okay?
- Yeah.

31:24.903 --> 31:26.270
I just, uh...

31:26.742 --> 31:29.342
I feel really bad for upsetting
you on the phone earlier.

31:29.367 --> 31:30.764
Oh, no, you didn't.

31:30.819 --> 31:32.717
I was going through my own thing.

31:33.727 --> 31:34.834
Okay.

31:35.940 --> 31:37.139
I just, I want...

31:37.928 --> 31:39.701
I want today to be perfect for you

31:39.726 --> 31:41.498
in every way that you've
ever dreamed about.

31:41.523 --> 31:43.928
And I know that sometimes
I can make you...

31:44.899 --> 31:45.959
You know...

31:47.415 --> 31:49.904
So I'm just... I want to stay
out of your way, okay?

31:56.318 --> 31:58.076
Mom, I know that our stuff...

31:58.470 --> 32:00.803
it can be complicated sometimes.

32:03.006 --> 32:04.193
But it's because...

32:04.570 --> 32:07.572
all that I've ever wanted
was to be like you.

32:10.051 --> 32:11.756
I want to be a singer like you.

32:12.171 --> 32:14.029
I want to be a mom like you.

32:15.429 --> 32:18.506
I want to have a marriage like yours.

32:22.095 --> 32:23.607
Mom, you are not...

32:24.042 --> 32:27.225
You are not in my way. You are my way.

32:28.976 --> 32:31.303
- Sweetheart...
- No. No cry...

32:31.553 --> 32:32.850
- No crying. We have to get to
- Okay, okay.

32:32.875 --> 32:35.146
- the wedding first before you cry.
- I know, but...

32:35.293 --> 32:37.717
♪ <i>Covered in everything</i> ♪

32:37.742 --> 32:41.311
- ♪ <i>Coveted all at once...</i> ♪
