♪ <i>Every inch of my love...</i> ♪

33:16.574 --> 33:19.639
JACK: <i>I'm sorry, baby, that's...
not really how it works.</i>

33:20.513 --> 33:21.779
But...

33:23.770 --> 33:25.571
But you want to know the exciting part?

33:26.387 --> 33:29.122
<i>One day, a long time from now,</i>

33:29.493 --> 33:32.139
<i>you're gonna meet someone
who's better than me.</i>

33:33.238 --> 33:37.068
<i>He's gonna be stronger and handsomer</i>

33:38.101 --> 33:39.889
<i>and even better at board games than me.</i>

33:39.914 --> 33:40.980
<i>(YOUNG KATE LAUGHS)</i>

33:41.159 --> 33:42.482
JACK: <i>And when you find him,</i>

33:42.712 --> 33:44.100
<i>when you find that guy,</i>

33:45.023 --> 33:46.657
that's the guy you're gonna marry.

33:46.762 --> 33:49.498
Oh, and he's one lucky guy,

33:49.816 --> 33:52.178
the guy that gets to marry you,
Katie girl.

33:54.493 --> 33:56.896
<i>And your mom and me,
we're gonna be there, you know.</i>

33:57.263 --> 33:58.584
<i>Just to check him out.</i>

33:59.564 --> 34:02.021
<i>Make sure he's as good at board games</i>

34:02.046 --> 34:03.568
<i>as you think that he is.</i>

34:03.593 --> 34:06.162
♪ <i>That you probably meant for us...</i> ♪

34:07.609 --> 34:09.154
And, assuming that he is,

34:11.722 --> 34:13.443
I'll get to walk you down the aisle.

34:15.870 --> 34:17.536
And I may even cry a little. (CHUCKLES)

34:17.813 --> 34:18.779
(CHUCKLES)

34:18.804 --> 34:21.193
♪ <i>And I saw the peaks on my own</i> ♪

34:22.013 --> 34:25.975
♪ <i>That you probably meant for us</i> ♪

34:26.815 --> 34:31.201
♪ <i>And I tore the fear from my bones</i> ♪

34:31.639 --> 34:35.678
♪ <i>That you probably never lost.</i> ♪

34:38.188 --> 34:39.318
♪

34:53.428 --> 34:54.592
Watch it.

34:58.702 --> 35:01.225
You know, I still don't
understand what Zoe said to her.

35:01.250 --> 35:03.351
Me neither. But who cares?

35:03.376 --> 35:04.928
- She's magic.
- Mm-hmm.

35:06.462 --> 35:07.818
- I told you.
- This is good.

35:07.843 --> 35:10.834
You three are Beth
and Randall's girls, right?

35:11.054 --> 35:12.334
Yes, we are.

35:12.398 --> 35:15.029
Oh, you two are the
spitting image of your mother.

35:15.118 --> 35:17.853
But you, you look just like your father.

35:17.982 --> 35:19.107
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

35:21.227 --> 35:22.694
So what's good over here, hmm?

35:31.466 --> 35:32.693
♪

35:39.301 --> 35:43.451
Uh... excuse me, everyone. Hi.

35:43.673 --> 35:46.865
I'm Kevin. I'm Kate's brother,
and it is toast time.

35:47.612 --> 35:48.803
So...

35:51.234 --> 35:52.412
Um...

35:56.810 --> 35:57.998
To, uh...

35:59.618 --> 36:03.451
My, uh, my brother and I
have been going,

36:03.476 --> 36:05.943
uh, well, a little bit crazy
the past couple of days.

36:05.968 --> 36:07.076
Um...

36:08.289 --> 36:10.209
W-We were going crazy
'cause we-we wanted make sure

36:10.234 --> 36:12.186
that this day was perfect for you, Kate.

36:13.608 --> 36:16.279
And the reason we wanted to make
sure this day was absolutely perfect

36:16.304 --> 36:18.545
for you is because that's...

36:20.225 --> 36:21.514
that's what Dad would've done.

36:21.539 --> 36:23.006
He would've made it perfect for you.

36:24.959 --> 36:26.084
And, uh...

36:26.396 --> 36:27.436
If he were here,

36:27.461 --> 36:29.287
he definitely would've looked at you

36:30.198 --> 36:32.084
and he would've said, "Katie girl...

36:34.381 --> 36:35.631
in your life...

36:35.884 --> 36:38.061
you have never looked more beautiful...

36:38.832 --> 36:40.264
than you do right now."

36:41.282 --> 36:43.061
And he would've been right, by the way.

36:43.772 --> 36:44.975
You're beautiful.

36:47.051 --> 36:50.725
Um... Mom, Randall,

36:50.750 --> 36:51.803
uh...

36:52.058 --> 36:55.029
earlier last year, Kate said
something to me that was,

36:55.465 --> 36:57.209
well, profound, uh...

36:58.286 --> 37:01.068
She said, "Kevin, if you
don't allow yourself to...

37:01.415 --> 37:03.146
to grieve Dad's death,

37:03.171 --> 37:06.053
it'll be like taking
a giant breath in and just...

37:06.853 --> 37:08.162
holding it there

37:09.508 --> 37:10.959
for the rest of your life."

37:13.235 --> 37:15.903
I... At the time, I didn't want
to hear any of that. You know...

37:16.623 --> 37:18.170
I... I didn't. Um...

37:18.195 --> 37:21.311
but here we are. It's one DUI
and a rehab stint later,

37:21.336 --> 37:24.071
and I-I'm-I'm thinking maybe
you were on to something

37:25.009 --> 37:27.154
- when you said that to me, um...
- (LIGHT CHUCKLES)

37:28.490 --> 37:31.623
I think we've all been
holding our breath

37:32.553 --> 37:34.795
for a long time. And, um...

37:35.108 --> 37:37.371
So before we toast Toby and Kate,

37:37.396 --> 37:38.597
before we clink our glasses,

37:38.622 --> 37:41.791
I think that the four of us should, uh,

37:41.874 --> 37:43.717
release that breath together.

37:45.804 --> 37:48.305
I think it's important that
we do that, that we just let go

37:48.330 --> 37:50.396
of those things we've
been holding onto, so...

37:51.817 --> 37:53.037
So here we go.

37:55.286 --> 37:56.497
(DEEP INHALE)

37:58.654 --> 38:00.045
(SLOW EXHALE)

38:02.709 --> 38:03.943
(DEEP INHALE)

38:04.429 --> 38:05.521
(SLOW EXHALE)

38:05.578 --> 38:06.732
(EXHALE)

38:07.690 --> 38:08.904
(EXHALING)

38:13.692 --> 38:14.927
- Okay.
- (LIGHT CHUCKLES)

38:16.142 --> 38:17.509
KEVIN: I, uh...

38:17.534 --> 38:18.842
I think my time is up.

38:19.752 --> 38:20.951
Um... (CLEARS THROAT)

38:22.540 --> 38:23.824
Toby, Kate...

38:25.428 --> 38:26.568
I love you both so much.

38:26.593 --> 38:28.646
I really do. I am so happy
for you. I'm proud.

38:28.671 --> 38:30.606
And I-I'm sorry my toast was weird.

38:31.062 --> 38:33.021
I'm not an expert on marriage at all,

38:33.046 --> 38:35.681
but, um, this next young gentleman is,

38:35.706 --> 38:37.857
my brother Randall. Please come save me.

38:38.421 --> 38:40.131
Save your brother. Come on, young man.

38:40.156 --> 38:42.771
Ladies and gentlemen, Randall Pearson,

38:43.236 --> 38:44.467
my brother.

38:44.492 --> 38:46.627
Oh man! You did good.

38:46.709 --> 38:47.904
There you go.

38:47.929 --> 38:49.193
(APPLAUSE)

38:49.284 --> 38:50.412
Um...

38:51.433 --> 38:55.631
Those of you who know me,
know that I'm big on control.

38:58.058 --> 39:00.607
It's taken me 37 years
to accept the fact

39:00.632 --> 39:02.311
that there's absolutely zero point

39:02.336 --> 39:04.139
in trying to control the future.

39:04.889 --> 39:06.553
<i>'Cause nobody knows where we'll be.</i>

39:08.103 --> 39:09.654
<i>Not even a year from now.</i>

39:10.318 --> 39:11.936
CAPTAIN (OVER P.A.):
<i>Well, folks, we'll be landing</i>

39:11.961 --> 39:14.256
<i>in Vietnam shortly, where it's a balmy</i>

39:14.281 --> 39:15.686
<i>85 degrees.</i>

39:16.406 --> 39:17.521
♪

39:25.772 --> 39:26.842
Hey, babe.

39:28.276 --> 39:29.865
I just spoke to the doctor.

39:29.890 --> 39:31.357
He wants you to come in tomorrow,

39:31.470 --> 39:33.029
talk about adjusting your meds.

39:36.573 --> 39:39.881
But... what we can control

39:40.617 --> 39:42.100
are the people we choose.

39:42.626 --> 39:43.701
Choosing our people

39:43.726 --> 39:47.115
is the closest we come
to controlling our destiny.

39:48.576 --> 39:49.795
Where's Deja?

39:51.155 --> 39:54.045
RANDALL: Because... while
everything else may change,

39:54.659 --> 39:56.350
<i>if you choose right,</i>

39:57.984 --> 39:59.576
your people will stay the same.

40:04.744 --> 40:06.131
Whether that's tonight

40:06.649 --> 40:08.467
<i>or a year from now,</i>

40:08.541 --> 40:11.428
<i>or ten years from now...</i>

40:13.342 --> 40:15.170
It's time to go see her, Tess.

40:16.618 --> 40:17.873
I'm not ready.

40:19.725 --> 40:20.920
Me neither.

40:24.990 --> 40:26.193
RANDALL: Katie girl,

40:26.620 --> 40:27.756
Tobias,

40:28.392 --> 40:29.764
when I look at you,

40:29.789 --> 40:33.186
I know in my bones
that in choosing each other,

40:34.386 --> 40:35.654
you have chosen

40:35.679 --> 40:36.912
perfectly.

40:39.023 --> 40:40.186
(SOFTLY): Yes.

40:40.359 --> 40:41.559
To Kate and Toby.

40:41.584 --> 40:43.018
Kate and Toby.

